<p>Reports <code>th:inline</code> attributes that are no longer needed in Thymeleaf 3.</p>

<p>Starting with Thymeleaf 3, inline output expressions <code>[[…]]</code> and <code>[(…)]</code> are evaluated in text content without an enclosing <code>th:inline</code> attribute. The attribute can be safely removed.</p>

<p>Example:</p>
<pre><code lang="html">
&lt;p <strong>th:inline="text"</strong>&gt;Hello, [[${name}]]!&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>After the quick-fix:</p>
<pre><code lang="html">
&lt;p&gt;Hello, [[${name}]]!&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>The inspection only reports the attribute when the project targets Thymeleaf 3.</p>
